This is also a good spot to post my thoughts on Kethite conversions. Mol masses are from our world elements. Densities are from Community Resource Pack and Real Fuels mods.

Kethite = C3H10N6O7 (242 g/mol & 3 kg/L)

UDMH = C2H8N2 (60 g/mol & 0.791 kg/L)

NTO = N2O4 (92 g/mol & 1.45 kg/L)

Oxygen = O2 (& 1.141 kg/L)

LqdHydrogen = H2 (2 g/mol & 0.07085 kg/L)

Hydrazine = N2H4 (32 g/mol & 1.004 kg/L)

LqdMethane = CH4 (16 g/mol & 0.42262 kg/L)

Loose C and N are treated as Waste

Loose H and O can be converted to Hydrogen, Oxygen, or Water

Kethite to hypergolic* fuels: 4x(C3H10N6O7) + ElectricCharge -> 5x(C2H8N2) + 7x(N2O4) + 2x©

others TBD

*Note: My Kerbal tech is using a 2.1 NTO to UDMH ratio, not the more efficient 2.61 ratio. We are not that advanced yet.
